== Early life and education ==
== Early life and education ==
Igor Shabalin was born in the town of [[Kamensk-Uralsky]], Sverdlovsk Oblast, USSR. After graduating from [[high school]] with a gold medal in 1967, Shabalin began studying [[Technology]] of Less-common, Dissipative and [[Radioactive decay|Radioactive]] Elements ([[Chemical engineering|Chemical Engineering]] for [[Nuclear industry|Nuclear Industry]]) in the Ural Polytechnic Institute ([[USTU-UPI]]), Sverdlovsk (now – [[Yekaterinburg]]). As a talented student, Shabalin attracted the attention of one of the leaders of the Soviet [[military industrial complex]] [[Dmitry Ustinov|D. F. Ustinov]],<ref>Newspaper edition "Uralskii rabochii", Sverdlovsk, USSR, Oct 1971 (in Russian) https://elib.uraic.ru/bitstream/123456789/6134/1/0010687.pdf Retrieved June 25, 2025</ref> who recommended him to the Deputy of [[the Supreme Soviet of the USSR]] for the city of Sverdlovsk, then - the [[Ministry of General Machine-Building|Minister of General Machine Building of the USSR]] [[Sergey Afanasyev (politician)|S. Almost immediately the analysis discovered and identified three names, the transport economist [[Ernest David Weiss]], [[Labour Party (UK)|Labour Party]] politician and [[Member of Parliament (United Kingdom)|Member of Parliament]] [[Wilfrid Vernon]] along with Frederick William Meredith, a Dublin engineer who were placed under surveillance.{{sfn|West|2005a|p=233}} Weiss was eventually interrogated and confessed to being a key Soviet agent and exposed a number of other Soviet agents operating in the UK.{{sfn|West|2005a|pp=234-235}} The papers also disclosed a number of code-names including JEAN, ELLEN, PROFESSOR and his wife SHIELA. JEAN was Robinsons chief agent who worked in London.{{sfn|Kesaris|1979|p=74}} According to the papers, JEAN forwarded intelligence to Robinson by mail and courier who then passed it to an agent LUX who delivered it to the Soviet embassy in [[Vichy]].{{sfn|West|2005a|p=235}} In June 1941, when Hitler invaded the Soviet Union and the Soviet embassy in Vichy closed, JEAN began to communicate by radio with Robinson.{{sfn|West|2005a|p=235}} This puzzled MI5 as no radio signals to the continent had been detected in Britain during the war.{{sfn|West|2005a|p=235}} Further evidence emerged in June 1941 from a cable from the [[Venona project]] that was partially decrypted that suggested that JEAN's codename had been choosen by a Russian and was likely active in London in June 1941, which was contrary to the statement that Weiss made. {{sfn|West|2005a|p=237}} This suggested that Weiss was actually JEAN although MI5 seemed to believe his statement and allowed him to remain in the UK.{{sfn|West|2005a|p=237}}
